FT  30 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Capital Inds to pay Pounds 7m for Samuel
Jones
Capital Industries, the financial services and industrial group, is to pay
Pounds 7m for Samuel Jones, which makes laminated paper products for
labelling and packaging.
Capital also said it would raise a total of Pounds 8.74m, through a
21-for-20 rights issue at 78p per share, to fund the acquisition and raise
net cash. Capital's shares closed 6p lower at 86p.
Rutland Trust, from which Capital Industries was spun off, has committed
Pounds 4.5m to underwriting the acquisition and is likely to raise its stake
in Capital from 37.4 per cent to 45 per cent. Mr Michael Langdon, deputy
chairman and chief executive of Rutland Trust, will join the board of
Capital as deputy chairman.
Capital meanwhile reported a pre-tax profit of Pounds 988,000 (Pounds
640,000) on turnover of Pounds 12.4m in the six months to June 30. Earnings
per share fell to 4.9p (7.3p). The interim dividend is 1.6p (nil).
